git init
git add <folder1> <folder2> <etc.>
git commit -m "Your message about the commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/yourUsername/yourRepository.git
git push -u origin master
git push origin master



// deploying nodejs app of heroku:

heroku -v
heroku login                   // do this in node app directory , if browser failed to open then copy the link and open it in the browser manually

heroku create name-of-app-which-will-be-the-subdomain-of-link     // give name with small letters only

and this is the step which you may have to do => heroku git:remote -a project-name

git push heroku master                           // app is deployed now..

suppose you made any change , then after making changes , you can see changes you made by git status
so now 
git add -A                 // for  updating repositry
git commit -m "commit message"          // to commit
and for updating the website     git push heroku master


// if any problem occur then create app on heroku dashboard first then , do follow the steps mention on heroku dashboard
